args:
Suddenly, the gang finds themselves in a
fishing competition as part of a plan to lure
Ebisu with his favorite food. But their catch
turns out bigger—and fresher—than expected,
and they find themselves in an all-out war with
a flailing fish that's fighting for freedom!
Ohhh... My stomach hurts sooo much...\nI can't go on! It's too much for me!
Stomach trouble again, Hanabusa?\nYou gonna be all right?
My anxieties are spinning out of control...\nI just want to go back to Hinomoto!\nWAAAAAAAAAH!
Hey now, no need for the waterworks!\nIf ya ask me, I bet yer gettin' all worked\nup about stuff what ain't even a big deal.
Ya just gotta let go and relax.\nWhatever happens is gonna happen.
I don't WANT to let go! If I fail to\naccomplish this mission, then...then I...
Easy now! You're gonna get your poor\nstomach all churned up again.

It's like this before every performance.
I practice again and again, my every
rehearsal flawless. But on the actual
day of the show...I blow it.
Even my own family treats me like\nsome delicate flower.
And then Mitsuhide thinks to honor ME\nwith performing in a foreign land?\nIf I fail at this, it will be my doom!

If you spent as much time envisioning
success as you did contemplating
failure, you could be the greatest
dancer the world has ever seen.
I give you the opportunity of a lifetime,\nand you'd rather spend your life limping\nalong on a trip to nowhere?
Geez, Hanabusa, calm down! I mean,\nyeah, Mitsuhide doesn't pull her punches,\nbut I'm sure she didn't mean all that.
No. Every word she spoke was true.\nWe must get those gifts back, now!
I'll simply have to stake my health upon it.\nI don't know if Ebisu will fall or I'll give\nout first, but either way...
I will dance the dance of life or death,\nfor the first—and possibly last—time!
Master Daikokuten! Let us execute\nthe plan we discussed earlier!
Whoa. Hanabusa seems like a\nchanged man all of a sudden.
Yeah, but I'm more curious what\nthis little plan of theirs is.
It's... Do do doooo! A fishing competition!\nYaaaaaaaay!
Ebisu's favorite food is fish.\nThis I learned from Daikokuten.
Hence, we will land a big fish,\nthen use it to land Ebisu himself!
So the plan is to use fish to\ncapture a cat...dragon.
Really? Well, if you say so.
Our plan is flawless in every facet.\nCan I count on all of you to help?
I'm not certain that ＂flawless＂ is\nthe best word for this plan...
Yeah, there's no way this doesn't\nhave some weird twist at the end.
I have a bite! To me, fish! To me!
I never imagined it would come\ntogether so smoothly!

Master, you must lend your aid as well as
verbal support! ...Also, the verbal bit could
REALLY use some work, if we're being
totally honest here.
Whoa! Daikokuten's rod looks like\nit's about to snap in half!
Hang on, buddy, or she'll pull ya in!
Do not let it get away, or I will cut the\nlot of you down where you stand!
Urrgggghhh... My arms are sooore...\nAnd my stomach huuurts!
Let's all pull on the count of three!\nReady? One...two...
The heck?! This fish is HUGE!
Look out! It's makin' its move!
To me, everyone! Cut this foe down!\nDo not let it escape the field of battle!
Dude, it's a FISH! You seriously need\nto chill over there, man.
Be you man or fish, the stakes are the\nsame. This is eat or be eaten, and the\nbattle has already begun!
Yeaaah, I don't think we're at any real risk\nof being eaten by a fish.
Stop nitpicking other people's battle cries\nand just finish this thing already!
Fine! I'll stow the snark and fight a shark!\n...Heh. Notte, you are GOOD.
C'mon, guys! Take out that smelly beast\nso I can chow down on sushi tonight!
